The paper deals with distributed graph algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The algorithms are designed for well-studied optimization problems such as Minimum Spanning Tree, Approximate Min-Cut, and Single Source Shortest Paths, which are commonly studied in the area of Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The algorithms also optimize for message complexity, which is a key aspect of Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the design and analysis of algorithms, which falls under the category of Algorithms (cs.AL). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of graph partitioning, which is a topic in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
